\\\\nI need to add a license to the project, so I'll use the write tool for that. But wait, before I do that, I should inspect the git status. It’s important to check what changes are currently in the repository to avoid any conflicts or surprises. I want to make sure everything is in the right place before proceeding with adding the license. Let’s get started on this the right way!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_eMxcT9AP4BBCtBdqUQ7dXiFO|fc_0804f64ea752bf540169ef83642e7c819e889b637e3a69edf0\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git status --short\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 541, \"output\": 767, \"cacheRead\": 16384, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 17692, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777304405692, \"responseId\": \"resp_0804f64ea752bf540169ef83561d54819ebc429054a32c0833\"}}\n1416:  ?? metadata/jdom/jdom/1.0/\n1418:  ?? metadata/jdom/jdom/1.0/\n1419:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_eMxcT9AP4BBCtBdqUQ7dXiFO|fc_0804f64ea752bf540169ef83642e7c819e889b637e3a69edf0\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"?? metadata/jdom/jdom/1.0/\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777304420625}}\n1420:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_eMxcT9AP4BBCtBdqUQ7dXiFO|fc_0804f64ea752bf540169ef83642e7c819e889b637e3a69edf0\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"?? metadata/jdom/jdom/1.0/\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777304420625}}\n1421:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating test class rules**\\n\\nI'm contemplating the rules regarding the one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files. It seems there might be a placeholder class that wasn’t generated, leading to the possibility of having two test files. I realize that the existing JdomTest doesn't map correctly and that JAXP tests shouldn't go there. Also, since all top-level test classes need to be public and there's a violation of this rule, maybe I should adjust that.\\n\\n**Evaluating test class adjustments**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to change the placeholder to a public empty class, especially since there are no JUnit tests. Removing JdomTest might simplify things by reducing unrelated placeholders. But I wonder if there should at least be one test. If we decide to delete it, does that affect our broader testing? \\n\\nThe final requirement for top-level test classes to be public could mean some might fail after the change. I think editing JdomTest to public could be the less invasive option.\\n\\n**Preparing to add license**\\n\\nI need to add a license to the project, so I'll use the write tool for that. But wait, before I do that, I should inspect the git status. It’s important to check what changes are currently in the repository to avoid any conflicts or surprises. I want to make sure everything is in the right place before proceeding with adding the license. Let’s get started on this the right way!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0804f64ea752bf540169ef835702f8819ebd697bd20ee7b580\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp74NkVPjjYJPAbzftSezF6l2mPbwvO1AcRrAt78XU4CfGmM0WA5FbFlIWzXIYrPrC3ymQmg7hrL6SBdEzF8mjs28jwH69RrnDW2Gb0M04EH53NNGnjOtAeUhgzjLB9PzmJKPNOkjb8KnyBFSnkWzPFkPaHgtNjN5y1bbxS2tMwtY9_wBtZiMuPIPN43QXH4W0kP4f6Jrdr_kj5uF-pPU363b-MbS35EWHwn6m95japQuyqDOiIlaqRcdTzQuyEohhGPgzsjiyokcCFcejJSquvfxYGwihv91ZlbNjyxg6l6KjilO50rLa-P9XktyVs-vdo05By5aDV1usIuMY5751bDaSQ2Ke5azDIq7I1MCgDNqm8PJnLexPrIL7R_02pdxnyry_ixOvJAqtAMTtqqDBOjlr1G4god1XudcucEW6KAm31Awwjbrkfh