validation is true, I also want to trigger the ErrorHandler. Could I assert that the parser receives the validation features? A stub could track this but maybe it’s not necessary. There might be a hidden need for coverage at line 74 only once. \n2830:[thinking] Focusing on this, I should just include getDocument. There should be a \"one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files,\" but there’s currently no XML4JDOMAdapterTest. This helper isn't a top-level test class, which is something I need to be aware of. \n2846:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering class fields**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether static class fields need to be initialized by an earlier failed run. Each test should be separate, right? It seems important to consider if we want to hit the class in the same JVM, as another test might interfere. It’s curious that none of them are using XML4J. Maybe I need to explore this further and double-check the dependencies to ensure everything is set correctly!\\n\\n**Analyzing XML parser needs**\\n\\nI'm thinking about a new test where using getDocument with a false trigger might connect to class$ java.lang.String and InputSource — seems sufficient. If validation is true, I also want to trigger the ErrorHandler. Could I assert that the parser receives the validation features? A stub could track this but maybe it’s not necessary. There might be a hidden need for coverage at line 74 only once. \\n\\nI need to create an org.apache.xerces.parsers.DOMParser, similar to Oracle's but with setFeature and setErrorHandler. This parser should handle namespace awareness based on the feature? It looks like the XML4JDOMAdapter sets namespaces to false. If the delegate factory has namespaceAware set to false, assertions regarding namespaces could fail. I want to understand how IBM/Xerces interprets the feature \\\"http://xml.org/sax