solve things. But I'm also considering that Method.invoke will require proper metadata.\\n\\n**Examining reflection analysis in GraalVM**\\n\\nI’m considering how GraalVM performs reflection analysis with constant patterns. It seems like using constructs like Class.forName(\\\"...\\\").getMethod(\\\"...\\\").invoke can be registered if the patterns are linear enough. I wonder if there are specific requirements to ensure this works correctly. Can I rely on this reflection method to function smoothly within the constraints of GraalVM? I’ll need to look into any limitations or best practices around this to ensure everything integrates properly!\\n\\n**Inspecting method patterns**\\n\\nI'm looking into the method names and parameter classes, specifically focusing on the constants. It feels like the native image agent might miss something if it's not static. The existing Oracle adapter seems to follow the same pattern and passes successfully. I think it might be helpful to inspect the OracleV2 source to see if there's an analogous situation, especially since there's no setFeature mentioned there. Let’s see what I can uncover!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_01aed8e892b2451d0169ef8e3286cc8197ad61e16e246f161d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp745EilntVrFswQt0WH95AMj-waZUv0k0F9P3EYmQxYS1LFFxWDJzdC0mXiLtKyUn43D0lWIIPyzme4w5rHK-tYNrUOYRKeY5L5lxHZllEliq5LFRKCzDL6dwi48oIRd7wfCs1eg6RS3RdbEn4oIfQDwGIw0WtpSef-_Euxd0n0kjri3PlbKc8yDAWKs0HObiZ78qnDGZPZ58XawFjcVuuFAKksSXKpirSmYj2QDySaZ-TwWRTz9tnDkpHAh-GooV4cpnIyr1zdLXcNtE44ved1boNdx6fCyoocoHuv699Z1ZkFTvoawazAgFBC1__ZLAH7jwk7Om387DIY2nDOXfPauTLesixeg6j3ylTl_XDe-TBSYjFzz8FJd7lzsEYvJfqFCrKGetmitbEAgQaZjijhpVwqNlQU9kgJg5N42NPPS1wuSiLtz2H9hGEepHdOksqa4h8l13X6SLA_gmd91yab2x44jYDaTHoVOmq3a2QXJFXJ4CWRJEA2XwGd-cREzgi6Q6sel6b7-FKd9S8Fq2RofHHl5kkZ54r1tTibDS0HWKu_ggXnOnwxnBOefC3fSe4B9lXNHPkLfF-NYGddpLCPRFIoNpCSOZBdphhv0dddYU1HdEXedf9jqhUbNtILsa11JXYgkNjSyAnEoD2nzRqTNGymv0NHLG1w_Gy7uIqzxRATL9JQ